34.1.hd_quote: Power is only great when its display or use serves the common good.
34.1.behavioral_axis: Shows power to deter threats; uses force only when survival or role demands it.
34.1.shadow_axis: Intimidation as identity; power not tied to service.

34.2.hd_quote: The ability when victory is in sight not to lose perspective.
34.2.behavioral_axis: Projects confident power and stays on mission when success is close.
34.2.shadow_axis: Power rush; emotionally carried away by winning.

34.3.behavioral_axis: Tests how much power can be shown before it breaks things.
34.3.shadow_axis: Showboating; performs power to cover insecurity.

34.4.hd_quote: The freedom in absolute victory to unlimited use of power.
34.4.behavioral_axis: After winning, wants space to wield power correctly and subtly.

34.5.behavioral_axis: Power is so projected it rarely must be used; when used, it ends resistance.
34.5.shadow_axis: Dictator paranoia; constant readiness to crush.

34.6.behavioral_axis: Recognizes that endless displays weaken power; withdraws to preserve it.
34.6.shadow_axis: Total withdrawal; power unused even when needed.
